snippet.textDisplay:
"First, I want to apologize directly to the young woman involved in this incident. I want to apologize to her for my behavior that night and for the consequences she has suffered in the past year. Although this year has been incredibly difficult for me personally, I can only imagine the pain she has had to endure. I also want to apologize to her parents and family members, and to my family and friends and supporters, and to the citizens of Eagle, Colorado.

I also want to make it clear that I do not question the motives of this young woman. No money has been paid to this woman. She has agreed that this statement will not be used against me in the civil case. Although I truly believe this encounter between us was consensual, I recognize now that she did not and does not view this incident the same way I did. After months of reviewing discovery, listening to her attorney, and even her testimony in person, I now understand how she feels that she did not consent to this encounter.

I issue this statement today fully aware that while one part of this case ends today, another remains. I understand that the civil case against me will go forward. That part of this case will be decided by and between the parties directly involved in the incident and will no longer be a financial or emotional drain on the citizens of the state of Colorado"

Rest in peace GREAT ONE with your beautiful daughter and all who died next to you.. My deepest condolences to Kobe family and all the families who lost someone on this sad day .. As I am a die hard Laker fan and a Kobe fan I have never wished for MY dreams to be F Ed up as I did Sunday, wishing all what happened to be one F'Ed up dream and when I wake up for it all to be normal.. Sadly with all what happened and I witnessed within such a short time IT WAS ALL SO REAL AND OVERWHELMING..With all what has happened..I must say '
Life is the greatest gift we human beings are blessed with and it sure is one awesome journey filled with so much of the unknown but with the desire to find out and then experience it ..Death is the most definite we human beings experience the same with no doubt, nothing can stop it.. Learn to live life with love and with very few regret and being none judgmental and with no hate.. As nothing we have we take when we die, we only take the good and the bad we did and do and will do as human beings.. Focus on self love with self respect ,so when you love anyone or anything it will be so genuine pure and real with respect..When I watched Kobe all these years.. He grew up to be one awesome human being not just a awesome player..With his desire to learn and be better in everyway' I deeply respect Kobe for his loyalty to the Lakers and giving twenty years of his precious life with such love with respect and dedication..Once again REST IN PEACE GREAT ONE AND THANK YOU FOR ALL WHAT YOU DID BEING YOU " SIMPLY AWESOME. ...Thank you for this video and whoever dislike this video has some serious learning to do about life ....TEARS ALL THE WAY !!

snippet.textDisplay:
My thoughts and prayers go out to Vanessa and her children it is unimaginable to lose both your husband and child within an instance. I know Vanessa and her children will never get past this but i hope they will find the strength to move forward and laugh at the memories that they have of Kobe and Giana. Although Time does make it better the scar is left behind and will continue to be their until the day you die. The impact that Kobe had on the NBA was insane and I truly believe we won’t see anything like it again, besides the impact and legacy he left on the court he also made an impact on kids around the world. He was a huge role model for the younger generation and will continue to be for upcoming generations. Although we are feeling sad we should be happy knowing that he is in a better place now. This tragedy will take a while to sink in. As of his daughter passing with him as well makes the tragedy way worse. I can’t even imagine how Kobe felt when he knew that his life was about to end as well as his daughter and he couldn’t do anything about it. This tragedy goes to prove that tomorrow is never promised and death can happen at any second, so if you haven’t told a loved one that you love them today then please do because you just don’t know if they could be gone the next day. Kobe & Gianna as well as the 7 other people on board will forever be in our hearts.

“Mamba out”

Kobe Bryant
August 23,1978-January 26,2020

Gianna Bryant
May 1,2006-January 26-2020

This is literally my very first time watching a video of Kobe Bryant, because when I heard the news about what happened to Kobe and his Daughter, I was left heartbroken and blank, like I didn't believe it at first and when I searched it up, it took me awhile for it to process and watching him now in this video feels soooo weird... I don't know if anyone feels the same but that's how I felt.😭💔🥀💔🥀 Rest in Paradise (Kobe & Gianna)🌅

Edit: I didn't know if I should say or do something, I stopped everything that I did on the day that I heard about it, I just sat on my sofa and stared at the wall, thinking about the news... I was like "Seriously, did it really happen?"
